Package ausroulette.model.wheel

Interface Pocket

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    PocketImpl
    public interface Pocket
    Represents a wheel pocket in the Aussie Roulette game in the Further Programming Assignment.

    You must not alter this interface.

    This interface should be implemented as PocketImpl.

    Author:
    Ross Nye
    See Also:
    PocketImpl, PocketColor, Wheel

      • toString

        java.lang.String toString()
        Generates a String representation of the pocket as seen in the supplied .log file.

        The String must match exactly the expected String. This will be tested during marking.

        Examples:

 Pocket:  #7 Red
 Pocket: #26 Black
 Pocket: #16 Red
